        <h2 class="h2 story__title">
          Built By Traders Who Got Tired Of The Industry’s <span class="accent">Broken Promises</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="story__copy">
          <p>TradeFundrr was founded by Christian Bose, a trader who had spent years inside the financial markets and understood what serious traders actually needed to perform at their best: real capital, fair rules, and a firm they could trust to pay them consistently. The prop firm model had real potential. The execution, almost everywhere, was falling short.</p>
          <p>The problem wasn't hard to identify. Across the industry, prop firms were collecting challenge fees from thousands of traders, running simulated accounts dressed up as real funding, and building business models that depended on traders failing rather than succeeding. Rules were written to catch people out. Payouts were delayed, disputed, or quietly denied. Support disappeared when traders actually needed it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>




