<section class="rules">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="eyebrow">the rules</p>
    <h2 class="h2"><span class="accent">Every rule explained.</span> <br>
    Every rule visible before you buy.</h2>
    <p class="lead">TradeFundrr's Rules Exist To Protect Your Payouts, Not To Catch You Out. Here's Every One Of Them…</p>
    <div class="rules__box short">
      <table>
        <tr>
          <th>rule</th>
          <th>why it exists</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>
            <span>Daily Loss Limit</span>
            <p class="smaller">Confirmed value</p>
          </td>
          <td>
            <p class="desc">Protects your account from a single bad session wiping out multiple days of gains. A daily cap on losses means one difficult trading day doesn't end your funded account, it's a safeguard, not a penalty.</p>
          </td>
        </tr>


        <tr>
          <td>
            <span>Maximum Drawdown</span>
            <p class="smaller">Confirmed value</p>
          </td>
          <td>
            <p class="desc">Defines the total loss threshold for the account. Drawdown limits exist in every professional trading environment. This one ensures the capital behind your account is protected and that payouts remain sustainable for all funded traders.</p>
          </td>
        </tr>


        <tr>
          <td>
            <span>Profit Target</span>
            <p class="smaller">Confirmed value</p>
          </td>
          <td>
            <p class="desc">Defines the performance threshold for payout eligibility. The profit target isn't arbitrary, it's the benchmark that confirms a trader has demonstrated a genuine, repeatable edge rather than reaching profitability through a single large position or outlier trade.</p>
          </td>
        </tr>


        <tr>
          <td>
            <span>Minimum Trading Days</span>
            <p class="smaller">Confirmed value</p>
          </td>
          <td>
            <p class="desc">Sets a floor on how quickly positions can be opened and closed. This exists to ensure funded trading reflects genuine market engagement rather than exploiting very short-term inefficiencies that don't apply in institutional trading environments.</p>
          </td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
          <td>
            <span>News Trading Rules</span>
          </td>
          <td>
            <p class="desc">The minutes around major news releases can produce price action that no risk management framework can reliably contain. This rule protects funded traders from breaching their loss limits through events outside their control, and protects TradeFundrr's ability to process payouts reliably.</p>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="hidden__rules">
      <span><img src="../assets/images/grey-check.svg" alt="grey-check"></span>
      <p>No hidden rules, no gotchas. Every TradeFundrr rule is visible before you buy, and every one of them is listed on the individual program pages…</p>
    </div>
    <a href="why-us.html" class="btn" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Have a rules question? Talk to our team<span class="arrow"><img src="../assets/images/btn-arrow.svg" alt="btn-arrow"></span></a>
